=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Luclin Agro on Healers</span><hr size=1> Has anyone else noticed an insane amount of agro in Luclin for healers?  I find I need to cast atone after every CH I cast.  Before Luclin I could cast one, stand for a few secs and then sit down.  Now, the mobs agro on me as soon as the spell lands.  Hell, I even get agro when casting Remedy or Divine Light.  Seems the only heal I can get off with no agro is Cel Heal.<br>
<br>
If this keeps up, I will need to invest some time in HoT getting those plate drops for AC.  My AC now is a paultry 891.<br>
<br>
One question.  I know that in the past, you could duel someone with a blue pet and your defense would go up.  Have they nerfed this?  My defense is only 180 and I wish to increase it.<br>
<br>
Uilaar Darkheartt<br>
54 Vicar<br>
Silent Avengers<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#D5D4D5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/umathii.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mathii</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Cyber Pimp</span><br> <font color=#000033>(12/13/01 10:33:53 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Luclin Agro on Healers</span><hr size=1> I noticed some ungodly heal aggro in SoL when I first went in.  It ended up to where if I had to heal someone after I slowed I may as well plan on tanking for a while. <br>
<br>
I think they may have fixed it though since it hasnt seemed to be quite so bad after the last couple patches.  Then again I have been soloing more so I cant be sure. <p><center> <img src="http://cleric.homestead.com/files/mathi.jpg
"> </center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#E5E5E6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ulaellanna.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Laellanna</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/image/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>I live here.... get out.</span><br> <font color=#000033>(12/13/01 1:30:29 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Luclin Agro on Healers</span><hr size=1> I haven't really noticed a huge increase in agro on healers personally... are you lower level than your tank?  Are you sitting when a mob is pulled to the camp?  I have noticed that those two things really make a difference in a few zones... the amount to which a healer's hate is increased also depends on zone/mob.<br>
<br>
Laellanna/Daena <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#D5D4D5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uuilarblakheart.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Uilar Blakheart</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>l33t d00d!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(12/13/01 5:43:47 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Luclin Agro on Healers</span><hr size=1> In 95% of the groups I am in, the tank is always of higher lvl.  I rarely sit down when a mob is coming to the camp.  The times I do sit, I am quickly reminded why I should not.<br>
<br>
Uilaar Darkheartt<br>
54 Vicar <br>
Silent Avengers <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#E5E5E6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/udollie.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dollie</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>p0\/\/3r-p0sT3r!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(12/13/01 11:21:42 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Luclin Agro on Healers</span><hr size=1> Went to Luclin all this evening(first time =p) and didnt notice anything bad about agro...except when i was sitting on a pull ...except for that it seems to work as usual for me.<br>
<br>
 <p><b><font face = "garamond" color="#E1C168">Celest<br>
High Nurse of the 60th bandaid<br>
Fallen Legacy<br>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#D5D4D5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ukayshasoulsinger.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kaysha Soulsinger</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>h0x0r!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(12/14/01 4:50:24 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Luclin Agro on Healers</span><hr size=1> Yesterday a guildgroup made it to Fungus Grove. The warrior (level 53) engaged a Deep Cavern Lotus (or something like that), and the Cleric (55) had to CHeal him four times before the Lotus was killed. Although the Lotus could summon (he summoned my brother once, lvl 55 Wizard), he never summoned the Cleric. The Cleric was a bit surprised at this. <p><br><A Href="http://www.guildmagic.com/character.cfm?ID=30878"><IMG
SRC="http://members.rott.chello.nl/ldirks/www/KayshaSoulsinger.jpg"></a><BR>
Vicar in the 53rd Circle of Erollisi Marr on Lanys T'Vyl <BR>
<i>The road to Heaven is paved with stones from Hell</i></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#E5E5E6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/umathii.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mathii</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Cyber Pimp</span><br> <font color=#000033>(12/14/01 5:22:17 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Luclin Agro on Healers</span><hr size=1> The second day it was out I went to Luclin and was fighting over in maidens. I slowed the mob as it was incoming, sicced pet and used epic, none of that did anything (it normally doesnt in any other zone) but just about every time I tossed a chloroblast on the my monk partner I got aggro.  <br>
<br>
I never sat down at that time (canni + regen + fungi) but there was some insane heal aggro.  Was in the same place a couple other times after that and now aggro seems to be about normal for kunark-style zones.  I think they fixed it. <p><center> <img src="http://cleric.homestead.com/files/mathi.jpg
"> </center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#D5D4D5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/umerkabaupon.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Merkaba UPoN</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>p0\/\/3r-p0sT3r!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(12/14/01 7:01:19 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Luclin Agro on Healers</span><hr size=1> I was noticing some diffrent agro as well.  Seemed to be tied to sitting.  I just stand during pulls now and wait for MA to grab agro. <p><center><img src="http://merkabaeq.homestead.com/files/merkabasig.gif"></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#E5E5E6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/u1ashlandd.showPublicProfile?language=EN>1ashlandd</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>p0\/\/3r-p0sT3r!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(12/14/01 7:33:18 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Luclin Agro on Healers</span><hr size=1> i kinda like the agro <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
beets the humdrum of heal med repeat<br>
<br>
dott heals may help counter this some sence you dont gain instant agro  but instead you gain agro as is goes <br>
<br>
ch would be about 900 agro points gained in one second <br>
and celestial elixar would be about 800 agro points gained in 24 seconds <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#D5D4D5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ulashannavalrynn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lashanna Valrynn</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_star.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>p0\/\/3r-p0sT3r!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(12/14/01 9:20:27 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://students.washington.edu/zip/eq/nicepika.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Luclin Agro on Healers</span><hr size=1> /nod it does seem to be more based around sitting.  I've been grouping with tanks under my lvl and you just have to make sure you don't sit on the pull  and then make sure the tank really has agro before you sit again.  I also notice I'm using more smaller heals then just CHing when i normally would...seems to help a bit. <p><center><img src="http://students.washington.edu/zip/eq/holidaysig.jpg"></center>

