"> </center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#D5D4D5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/usavilashkevron.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Savil Ashkevron</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>h0x0r!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(12/16/01 2:00:45 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Luclin Agro on Healers</span><hr size=1> Uilar, i'm not sure 'bout the pet thing being nerfed, but you need to go in and get hit by a few dozen mobs occasionally, on low maintenance groups.  Go in and tank some to get rid of the boredom and such, My Offense is maxed at 200, my 1hb is maxed at 175, and my defense is 198, 2 points from max, but can't seem to get it to go up anymore.<br>
<br>
As for the luclin thing, root it if ya can, then go ahead and med/CH or whatever.  My heal style seems different than most though as in I don't let my tanks get below 3 bubbles of health unless they specifically request it. <p><BR>
Savil Ashkevron -Mischievious Cleric of Bristlebane and the MnM pack<BR>
47 lvls of healin and toe smashin<BR>
Naggy - 3; Vox - 2; PoH - 7; PoF - 1; PoA - 0; PoG - 1; PoM - 0<BR>
<BR>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#E5E5E6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ulittlecherub.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Little Cherub</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Cyber Pimp</span><br> <font color=#000033>(12/17/01 7:42:57 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Luclin Agro on Healers</span><hr size=1> Heh Savil, in a couple levels start complete healing, it'll be a lot more efficient than superior healing.  I'd suggest if you group with post 50's warriors to start practicing c heals now.  Try to time it to land when they're under 1 red, then once you get the hang of that, under half a red.  If you don't, you'll always be oom higher levels because you simply have to be mana efficient or exp is slow as mollasses.<br>
<br>
